<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
2.5-4.8 mm, 1.7-2.8
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ã—">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide, body usually stout and darkly colored. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hopkins" authorityYear="1915" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Ambrosiodmus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ambrosiodmus" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ambrosiodmus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the pronotum short and rounded, types 1 or 2 in dorsal view; pronotal disc entirely asperate; pronotum anterior margin without a carina or serrations; elytral disc convex; declivity rounded and steep at apex; antennal club flattened, type 4; scutellum flat, flush with elytra; mycangial tufts absent; and procoxae contiguous.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
